#guide for syncing zotero across ecosystems (mac and linux)
#see this resource
#https://peterfalkingham.com/2025/04/15/setting-up-zotero-with-onedrive-dropbox-google-drive-etc/
#


select cloud storage.
setup zotero as is on primary machine
Mac
>settings> advanced> linkedattachement base dir .
change the linked dir to the cloud location

Download Zotmoov plugin(xpi file)

>Tools >plugin> add Zotmoov plugin
Plugin tab should appear in settings
> change the directory to the linked dir specified earlier

on secondary machine.
>repeat same process

#watchout

ensure that the file path on linux matches the file path on mac

you can use an fstab entry with bind mounts

sample fstab entry
#fixing zotero
#19 December 2025
/home/omokayj/gDriveOmokayj  /Users/omokayj/Library/CloudStorage/GoogleDrive-omokayodejohn@gmail.com/My\040Drive  none  bind  0  0


